<a name="662"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Well</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Thott on Monday, March 05 @ 07:13:07 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Thott">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>FoH hasn't killed Yelinak for the same reason noone else has killed Yelinak: his swing delay was decreased.<br>
<br>
I'm guessing this was done as a temporary difficulty increase back before the bounding box was changed, and simply wasn't removed.<br>
<br>
He currently isn't killable.<br>
<br>
The warders in sleeper's tomb are also unkillable.<br>
<br>
Verant is in the business of providing content.  If Verant does not add content, then they can certainly expect players to be unhappy.  What reaction do they expect players to have, if they REMOVE content (Yelinak, warders, BP's, Klandicar, etc.)?<br>
<br>
I personally don't care about the cleric hate change.  I care about being able to experience new content.  In EQ, that involves KILLING that content.  Now, for some of that content, I no longer can.  That bothers me.  The primary argument against the cleric "nerf" is that it will make killable things unkillable.  For us, this hasn't proven to be true (DA tanking compensates).  <br>
<br>
In the next patch the healing aggro will be reduced, but from what I've heard, it will simply raise the amount of damage/sec a cleric has to heal before they out aggro the tank.  For us that still means we will have clerics tanking, because if clerics EVER out-taunt a tank, they will do it with us.  Verant is also reducing the aggro generated by sitting, which will seriously reduce DA tanking.  THIS change may actually result in the removal of content, i.e. we won't be able to kill things that we can now.  We'll see.<br>
<br>
Having my clerics be tanks just makes for a silly game.  It's obviously non-sensical, and easy to point at and say "this is wrong, fix it."  Non-sensical things should certainly be fixed, but the real issue here is content.<br>
<br>
--Thott<br>
Guildleader<br>
<br>
</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=111&pid=626&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p></ul></p><a name="664"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Well smart ass, you still havent posted your name guild..</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Pilferr on Monday, March 05 @ 07:57:04 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Pilferr">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>But in answer to your question, we've been in this other zone you MAY have read about (i'm thinking you probably have, as you seem to be a well versed reader of eqlizer/eqlore etc..) called Veeshans Temple..sound familiar? Well, it seems that armor drops there for the Kael armor quests. Thats where we've been.<br>
